flowRoot.flowPara: 1. Select your solar system and body
2. Enter how many satellites are in your launch bundle
3. Enter a target altitude OR orbital period for your deployed network. Default is minimum orbit altitude/period.
4. The results will display deployment orbit.
4a. Launch your bundle to the eccentric deployment orbit.
4b. Each periapsis detach 1 satellite and circularize.
4c. Repeat until your out of satellites. Deorbit your junk.
Being accurate with your orbit time period is far more important than matching altitude exactly.
2 satellites can have slightly varrying orbits, but if they're period is the same they will never drift.
Make sure to compensate for decouplers and adjust your period back after each satelitte stage event. If your deploy period is 4hrs, keep it there +/- 0.5sec.
Satellites should be within 0.05sec of desired orbit period to reduce drift.
